        public void drawActionBubbleLoop(java.awt.Graphics2D g,
                                 int x,
                                 int y,
                                 int r)
        Draws and fills the action bubble on the center of the transition (not for self loops).
        Parameters:
        g - the graphics to draw with.
        x - x-coordinate for the center of self-loop.
        y - y-coordinate for the center of self-loop.
        r - the radius of the self-loop.

      • drawActionBubble

        public void drawActionBubble(java.awt.Graphics2D g,
                             int x1,
                             int y1,
                             int x2,
                             int y2)
        Draws and fills the action bubble on the center of the transition (not for self loops).
        Parameters:
        g - the graphics to draw with.
        x1 - x-coordinate for the center of the start state bubble.
        y1 - y-coordinate for the center of the start state bubble.
        x2 - x-coordinate for the intersection of the transition with the end state bubble.
        y2 - y-coordinate for the intersection of the transition with the end state bubble.
